Class GExporter

java.lang.Object
org.interworldtransport.cladosG.GExporter
public class GExporter extends Object
This is a non-constructable class meant as a collector of all export methods for cladosG objects They are collected here not because a single object doing data exports is particularly efficient, (it is likely to be a bottleneck until everything is parallelized), but because the geometry objects in real physical models are likely to be numerous. The geometry does not need to take up memory knowing how to export its contents to some format for every single piece of geometry. It is enough that one object does it or even that it is all handled by static methods.

      public static final String toJSON(Foot pF)
      Export a Foot as a small JSON fragment. Object properties are represented as attributes. This is intended as an output format.

      {
      "Foot": {
      "name": "NamedPoint"
      }
      }

      Parameters:
      pF - Foot to be exported as JSON
      Returns:
      String formatted as JSON containing information about the input

    • toJSON

      public static final String toJSON(Blade blade, boolean pAsText)
      Export a Blade as a small JSON fragment. Object properties are represented as attributes. This is intended as an output format.

      Example:
      {
      "Blade": {
      "key": 81985529216486895,
      "bitKey": "0b111111111111111",
      "generators": ["E1","E2","E3","E4","E5","E6","E7","E8","E9","EA","EB","EC","ED","EE","EF"]
      }
      }

      Parameters:
      blade - Blade to be exported as JSON
      pAsText - boolean determines whether generators are exported in text or ordinal representation.
      Returns:
      String formatted as JSON containing information about the input

      public static final String toJSON(Basis basis)
      Export a Basis as a JSON fragment. Object properties are represented as attributes. This is intended as an output format.

      Example:
      {
      "basis": {
      "UUID": "6f264df4-0b45-4ac2-9679-3ff1d181a0dc",
      "Grades": {
      "count": 3,
      "grade": [ {"rank": 0, "range": "0-0"},
      {"rank": 1, "range": "1-2"},
      {"rank": 2, "range": "3-3"}]
      },
      "Blades": {
      "count": 4,
      "blade": [ {"key": 0, "bitKey": "0b00", "generators": []},
      {"key": 1, "bitKey": "0b01", "generators": ["E1"]},
      {"key": 2, "bitKey": "0b10", "generators": ["E2"]},
      {"key": 5, "bitKey": "0b11", "generators": ["E1","E2"]}]
      }
      }
      }

      String formatted as JSON containing information about the input

    • toXMLOrdString

      public static final String toXMLOrdString(Blade blade, String indent)
      This method produces a printable and parseable string that represents the Blade in a human readable form.
      This variation uses a Generator's ordinal to name it in the generator list.
      Parameters:
      blade - The Blade to be exported to XML.
      indent - String of 'tab' characters that help space the output correctly visually. It's not actually necessary except for human readability of the output.
      Returns:
      String The XML formated String representing the Blade.
